<SLUG> BC-BOX-AYALA-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TOP RANK OFFICIALS HOPE TO SEE AYALA ON SHOWTIME, HBO
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JESSE SANCHEZ 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ Moments after successfully defending his
World Boxing Association bantamweight title with a unanimous
decision against Saohin Srithai Condo on Saturday at Will Rogers
Coliseum, a victorious Paulie Ayala chuckled in his dressing room.
</P>
<P>
   Sporting bruises on his ears and wounds on the left side of his
swollen face, the champion was forced to do something he rarely
does _ turn down an autograph seeker.
</P>
<P>
   After 12 rounds of throwing left hooks and uppercuts to the
right side of Condo's face, Ayala's dominant hand sat swollen in a
bucket of ice water. He couldn't sign an autograph if he wanted to.
</P>
<P>
   ``He \RCondo\S had a hard face,'' said Ayala, who improved to
29-1, with 12 knockouts. ``I wasn't hitting him on the top of the
head; I was hitting him with uppercuts.''
</P>
<P>
   I guess it's where they got the saying `it's going to hurt me a
lot more than it's going to hurt you.' ''
</P>
<P>
   Ayala's left hand was examined by a doctor yesterday, but X-rays
showed no signs of broken bones. He did, however, bleed from the
nose in the ring for the first time since his nose was originally
broken in 1986.
</P>
<P>
   His bumps, bruises, and more importantly, victories, are not
going unnoticed, said Lee Samuels spokesman for Top Rank Inc.,
Ayala's promotional team. By defeating Johnny Tapia for the title
and successfully defending against Condo, Ayala has established
himself as a legitimate star with 24 consecutive rounds of
excitement, Samuels said.
</P>
<P>
   ``He took a giant step against Tapia, another against Condo, and
he is the only action fighter out there right now, '' Samuels said.
``I will personally call Nigel Collins \Reditor of Ring Magazine\S
and let him know about Paulie.''
</P>
<P>
   Samuels said Top Rank Inc., is nominating Ayala-Tapia and
Ayala-Condo for The Ring Magazine's Fight of the Year, along with
Ayala as Fighter of the Year. Ayala is the only nominee in either
category for the organization, who also promotes Oscar De La Hoya
and Floyd Mayweather.
</P>
<P>
   Top Rank Inc., will also be pursuing contracts with HBO and
Showtime for Ayala, according to matchmaker Bruce Trampler.
</P>
<P>
   ``What I propose to do is to send cassettes to HBO and Showtime
people, and try and interest them, '' Trampler said. `` They both
said they are trying to go Hispanic, and Ayala typifies where they
should be. Regardless, it's not a matter of who he fights anymore,
it's for whom he fights.''
</P>
<P>
   Trampler also said there could be more championship bouts in
Fort Worth for Ayala, and Top Rank Inc., is considering making the
city synonymous with Ayala's career on a national level.
</P>
<P>
   ``Why not?, Trampler said. ``Romero has Albuquerque, Paulie has
Fort Worth. It could work. ''
</P>
<P>
   As for the champion, he will not fight until next year, and
remains confident about his future in the ring.
</P>
<P>
   ``I proved I'm a force to be reckoned with, a champion to be
reckoned with,'' Ayala said. ``I've always said it from the
beginning, I just needed the opportunity. Now that I have it, I'm
going to make the best of it.''
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
