<BODY>
 AM-NYT-BUDGET  
(gm) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; FOR TUESDAY AMs &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Here are today's top news stories from The New York Times News
Service for AMs of Tuesday, Oct. 26:
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL &LR;  (``i'' code)
</P>
<P>
   GAZA-WESTBANK (Dateline to kum) _ As Israel opens a 27-mile safe
passageway for Palestinians, linking Gaza and the Westbank,
desperate Gazans head to a ``land of plenty'' _ the West Bank,
where they can make $3 a day instead of $1 a day. By Deborah
Sontag.
</P>
<P>
   And
</P>
