<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-PUMPKIN-MAIN-LADN, </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>


</HEADLINE>
 2nd add 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients)  LOS ANGELES: powdered sugar until fluffy. 
 
 
PUMPKIN PECAN PIE 
 
PUMPKIN LAYER: 
1 cup 100 percent pure pumpkin (puree) 
1/3 cup granulated sugar 
1 large egg 
1 teaspoon pumpkin pie spice 
1 unbaked 9-inch deep-dish pie shell (4 cup volume) 
PECAN LAYER: 
2/3 cup light corn syrup 
1/2 cup granulated sugar 
2 large eggs 
3 tablespoons butter OR margarine, melted 
1/2 teaspoon vanilla 
1 cup pecan halves
<TEXT>
<P>
   For Pumpkin Layer, combine pumpkin, sugar, egg and pumpkin pie
spice in a medium bowl; stir well. Spread over bottom of pie shell.
</P>
<P>
   For Pecan Layer, combine corn syrup, sugar, eggs, butter and
vanilla in same bowl; stir in nuts. Spoon over pumpkin layer.
</P>
<P>
   Bake in preheated 350-degree oven 50 minutes, or until knife
inserted in center comes out clean. Cool on wire rack. Makes 8
servings. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
ICED PUMPKIN BLONDIES &QC; 
 &QL; 
2 1/4 cups all-purpose flour &QL; 
2 1/2 teaspoons baking powder &QL; 
2 teaspoons ground cinnamon &QL; 
1/4 teaspoon salt &QL; 
1 1/2 cups packed brown sugar &QL; 
3/4 cup (1 1/2 sticks) butter OR margarine, softened &QL; 
1 teaspoon vanilla &QL; 
2 large eggs &QL; 
1 cup 100 percent pure pumpkin (puree) &QL; 
Maple Icing
</P>
<P>
   Grease a 15x10-inch jellyroll pan.
</P>
<P>
   Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt in a medium
bowl. Beat brown sugar, butter and vanilla in a large mixer bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in
pumpkin. Gradually beat in flour mixture. Spread into prepared pan.
</P>
<P>
   Bake in preheated 350-degree oven 20 to 25 minutes or until
wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool completely in
pan; spread with Maple Icing. Cut into bars. Makes 5 dozen.
</P>
<P>
   MAPLE ICING: Beat 6 ounces softened cream cheese, 2 tablespoons
softened butter OR margarine and 2 cups sifted powdered sugar in a
small mixer bowl until smooth. Add 1 to 2 teaspoons maple
flavoring. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
PUMPKIN SMOOTHIE &QC; 
 &QL; 
1 can (15 ounces) 100 percent pure pumpkin (puree), chilled &QL; 
1 can (12 ounces) evaporated milk, chilled &QL; 
1 1/2 cups orange juice &QL; 
1/2 cup (1 small) sliced banana &QL; 
1/3 cup packed light brown sugar &QL; 
Ice cubes (optional) &QL; 
Ground cinnamon (optional)
</P>
<P>
   Combine pumpkin, evaporated milk, orange juice, banana and brown
sugar in blender container. Cover; blend until mixture is smooth.
Pour over ice. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Makes 6 servings. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
QUICK PUMPKIN PUDDING &QC; 
 &QL; 
1 package (about 5 ounces) INSTANT vanilla pudding and pie filling
mix &QL; 
1 can (12 ounces) evaporated milk OR 1 1/2 cups regular milk &QL; 
1 can (15 ounces) 100 percent pure pumpkin (puree) &QL; 
1 teaspoon pumpkin pie spice &QL; 
Whipped cream
</P>
<P>
   Beat pudding mix and evaporated milk according to package
directions in a large bowl. Chill 5 minutes. Add pumpkin and
pumpkin pie spice; mix well. Spoon into dessert dishes. Chill 10
minutes or until ready to serve. Top with whipped cream before
serving. Makes 8 servings. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
FROZEN PUMPKIN TORTE &QC;
</P>
<P>
   A wonderful dessert that may be made ahead of time and stored in
the freezer until needed. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
CRUST: &QL; 
1 cup finely chopped pecans &QL; 
1 cup finely crushed gingersnap cookies (about 16) &QL; 
2 tablespoons packed light brown sugar &QL; 
1/4 cup butter OR margarine, melted &QL; 
FILLING: &QL; 
1 can (15 ounces) 100 percent pure pumpkin (puree) &QL; 
1 cup packed light brown sugar &QL; 
1 1/2 teaspoons ground cinnamon &QL; 
1 teaspoon ground nutmeg &QL; 
1/8 teaspoon ground ginger &QL; 
1 cup whipping cream, whipped &QL; 
1 quart French vanilla ice cream &QL; 
GARNISH: &QL; 
Whipped cream (optional) &QL; 
Chopped pecans (optional)
</P>
<P>
   For Crust, in a bowl, combine pecans, cookie crumbs, brown sugar
and butter; blend well. Pat evenly into bottom and 3/4 up side of a
9-inch springform pan. Freeze.
</P>
<P>
   For Filling, in a small saucepan, combine pumpkin, brown sugar,
cinnamon, nutmeg and ginger. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly,
about 4 minutes; chill. Fold whipped cream into pumpkin mixture.
</P>
<P>
   To assemble, slightly soften ice cream; spoon into crust-lined
pan, pressing evenly into bottom with spatula. Layer pumpkin
mixture over ice cream. Freeze 5 to 6 hours or overnight. Remove
side of pan before serving. Garnish with whipped cream and chopped
pecans. Makes 1 (9-inch) torte. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
HARVEST BREAD PUDDING &QC; 
 &QL; 
8 to 10 slices cinnamon raisin bread, crust removed &QL; 
3 eggs &QL; 
1 can (15 ounces) 100 percent pure pumpkin (puree) &QL; 
2 cups milk &QL; 
3/4 cup granulated sugar &QL; 
1/2 teaspoon ground cinnamon &QL; 
1/2 teaspoon pumpkin pie spice &QL; 
1/4 teaspoon salt &QL; 
1/2 cup raisins &QL; 
Whipped cream (optional)
</P>
<P>
   Place bread on cookie sheet. Bake in preheated 350-degree oven 5
minutes. Turn; bake an additional 3 to 5 minutes or until dry.
Remove from oven; cool. Cut into 1-inch cubes (should measure about
4 cups); set aside.
</P>
<P>
   In a large mixer bowl, beat eggs. Add pumpkin, milk, sugar,
cinnamon, pumpkin pie spice and salt; mix well. Stir in bread
cubes. Allow to set 5 minutes. Stir in raisins. Pour into buttered
1 1/2-quart baking dish.
</P>
<P>
   Bake in preheated 350-degree oven 1 hour 20 minutes to 1 hour 30
minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean. Serve
warm. Top with whipped cream, if desired. Makes 1 1/2-quart
casserole. &UR;  &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
MORE &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
