r d BC-PUMPKIN-MAIN-LADN 3rdadd   10-25 0608
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-PUMPKIN-MAIN-LADN, </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>


</HEADLINE>
 3rd add 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients)  LOS ANGELES: Makes 1 1/2-quart casserole. 
 
 
PUMPKIN APPLE STREUSEL MUFFINS 
 
2 1/2 cups all-purpose flour 
2 cups sugar 
1 tablespoon pumpkin pie spice 
1 teaspoon baking soda 
1/2 teaspoon salt 
2 eggs, lightly beaten 
1 cup 100 percent pure pumpkin (puree) 
1/2 cup vegetable oil 
2 cups, peeled, finely chopped apples 
Streusel Topping
<TEXT>
<P>
   In a large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients; set aside. In a
medium bowl, combine eggs, pumpkin and oil. Add liquid ingredients
to dry ingredients; stir just until moistened. Stir in apples.
Spoon batter into greased or paper-lined muffin cups, filling 3/4
full. Sprinkle Streusel Topping over batter.
</P>
<P>
   Bake in preheated 350-degree oven 35 to 40 minutes or until
toothpick comes out clean. Makes 18 muffins.
</P>
<P>
   STREUSEL TOPPING: In a small bowl, combine 2 tablespoons
all-purpose flour, 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon ground cinnamon.
Cut in 4 teaspoons butter until mixture is crumbly. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
SOUR CREAM PUMPKIN COFFEECAKE &QC; 
 &QL; 
1/2 cup butter OR margarine &QL; 
3/4 cup plus 1/3 cup sugar &QL; 
1 teaspoon vanilla &QL; 
4 eggs &QL; 
2 cups all-purpose flour &QL; 
1 teaspoon baking powder &QL; 
1 teaspoon baking soda &QL; 
1 cup dairy sour cream &QL; 
1 can (15 ounces) 100 percent pure pumpkin (puree) &QL; 
1 teaspoon pumpkin pie spice &QL; 
Streusel
</P>
<P>
   Cream butter, 3/4 cup sugar and vanilla in mixer bowl. Add 3
eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
</P>
<P>
   Combine flour, baking powder and baking soda. Add dry
ingredients to butter mixture alternately with sour cream. Combine
pumpkin, remaining 1 egg, beaten, remaining 1/3 cup sugar and pie
spice. Spoon 1/2 of batter into 13x9x2-inch baking dish; spread to
corners. Sprinkle 1/2 of Streusel over batter. Spread pumpkin
mixture over Streusel. Carefully spread remaining batter over
pumpkin mixture. Sprinkle remaining Streusel over top.
</P>
<P>
   Bake in preheated 325-degree oven 50 to 60 minutes or until
toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Makes 12 servings.
</P>
<P>
   STREUSEL: Cut 1 cup packed brown sugar, 1/3 cup butter and 2
teaspoons ground cinnamon together until blended; stir in 1 cup
chopped walnuts OR pecans. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
MAPLE PECAN PUMPKIN CHEESECAKE &QC; 
 &QL; 
CRUST: &QL; 
1 3/4 cups pecan shortbread cookie crumbs (about 12 to 14 cookies) &QL; 
4 teaspoons butter OR margarine, melted &QL; 
1/2 cup chopped pecans &QL; 
CHEESECAKE: &QL; 
3 packages (8 ounces EACH) cream cheese, softened &QL; 
1 1/4 cups packed brown sugar &QL; 
1 can (15 ounces) 100 percent pure pumpkin (puree) &QL; 
2 eggs &QL; 
2/3 cup undiluted evaporated milk &QL; 
2 tablespoons cornstarch &QL; 
1 1/2 teaspoons maple flavoring &QL; 
1/2 teaspoon ground cinnamon &QL; 
TOPPING: &QL; 
1/2 cup chopped pecans &QL; 
1/4 cup packed brown sugar &QL; 
2 tablespoons butter, melted &QL; 
1/4 teaspoon maple flavoring
</P>
<P>
   For Crust, in a small bowl, combine cookie crumbs and butter.
Press onto bottom and 1-inch up sides of a 9-inch springform pan;
sprinkle with pecans. Bake in preheated 350-degree oven 6 to 8
minutes. Do not allow to brown. Remove from oven; cool.
</P>
<P>
   For Cheesecake, in a large mixer bowl at medium speed, beat
cream cheese and brown sugar until creamy. Add pumpkin, eggs,
undiluted evaporated milk, cornstarch, maple flavoring and
cinnamon; beat well. Pour into prepared crust. Bake in preheated
350-degree oven 55 minutes or until edge is set.
</P>
<P>
   For Topping, combine pecans, brown sugar, butter and maple
flavoring in a small bowl. Sprinkle over surface of cheesecake.
Return cheesecake to 350-degree oven 5 to 10 minutes, or until
topping is bubbly. Cool on wire rack. Chill several hours or
overnight. Makes 12 to 16 servings. &UR;  &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
END &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
