Michael Curley, the two-fisted Massachusetts politician. By Martin
Nolan. 1,500 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BUSINESS-BOOKS (Undated) _ David Wilcox wants to create the
Cliffs Notes of business books with an on-line database service for
that distills 400 recent books on business. By Ronald Rosenberg.
880 words. PHOTO
</P>
<P>
   FINANCE-HOOKER (undated) _ Market timing in 401(k) is not a good
idea. By Kenneth Hooker.
</P>
