<P>
   BUCHANAN-2000 (Washington) _ Pat Buchanan, the firebrand
conservative who worked for three Republican presidents and won the
New Hampshire GOP primary in 1996, leaves his party and announces
he will seek the Reform Party nomination. That's troubling news for
Republican front-runner George W. Bush as polls show Buchanan
putting the same drag on his candidacy as Reform nominee Ross Perot
did to his father, President George Bush, in 1992. By BENNETT ROTH.
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-2000 (Austin, Texas) _ Texas Gov. George W. Bush releases
the first four ads of his presidential campaign in Iowa and New
Hampshire as polls show him struggling there against rivals who
have done far more campaigning. All the ads, including one in
Spanish, focus on the issues and biographical information about the
Republican candidate. By CLAY ROBISON.
