   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   CRASH-JET (Houston) _ A Lear jet with golf champion Payne
Stewart and four others aboard crashes after an uncontrolled flight
from Florida. The jet, which was scheduled to land in Texas,
crashed in South Dakota. Stewart was to play in the Tour
Championships golf tournament in Houston this week. By TONY
FREEMANTLE.
</P>
<P>
   JASPER-TRIAL (Jasper, Texas) _ Jury selection begins in the
trial of Shawn Berry, the third defendant in the brutal slaying of
James Byrd. Jr. near Jasper last year. Two other men were convicted
and sentenced to die for their part in the murder. By RICHARD
STEWART.
</P>
<P>
   INTERNATIONAL NEWS (``i'' category)
</P>
<P>
   ISRAEL-SAFE-PASSAGE (Erez Crossing, Gaza Strip) _ Israel opens a
land link between the Palestinian-controlled West Bank and Gaza
Strip _ a long-anticipated move that takes Palestinians a step
closer to statehood and boosts confidence in the peace process. By
DEBORAH HORAN.
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   GLF-PROFILE (Houston) _ He first burst onto the scene and into
our consciousness because of his colorful and distinctive attire,
but Payne Stewart made a name for himself on the golf course as
well with three major championships and a stellar career. By JAYNE
CUSTRED.
