<P>
   UNDATED _ A new treatment is being used for patients with liver
cancer: Laparoscopic thermal ablation of cancerous tumors in the
liver _ or Radiofrequency Interstitial Tissue Ablation (RITA) _ as
the new minimally invasive treatment is named, uses heat to burn
the tumor away. The technique offers hope to people with cancer in
the liver, especially the estimated 75 percent whose tumors cannot
be surgically removed at diagnosis. By CAROLYN POIROT. Story will
move in ``l'' lifestyle category. Accompanied by
