<P>
   ISRAEL-EVANGELICALS (Jerusalem) _ Israelis arrest 22 evangelical
Christians who have been staying in Israel and praying nightly on
the Mount of Olives in anticipation of the second coming at the
Millennium, saying it will deport the group over visa violations.
By Charles Sennott. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   SAFRICA-TRUTH (Pretoria) _ The Truth and Reconciliation
Commission weighs recalling Botha and de Klerk on grounds that they
knew of killings that they did not disclose in previous testimony.
By Kurt Shillinger. 600 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WASHINGTON (w) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CHAFEE-OBIT (Washington) _ Sen. John Chafee of Rhode Island dies
at 77. The longtime senator and former governor earned praise even
from Democrats for his moderate stance on issues. By Anne Kornblut.
1,000 words.
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   CHAFEE-AWARD (Boston) _ John Chafee was to have received a ``New
Englander of the Year'' award Monday night in Boston. The ceremony
continues without him. By Ellen Barry.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BUCHANAN-REFORM (Undated) _ The conservative firebrand bolts
from the Republican Party for the Reform Party. By Bob Hohler. 900
words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; BUSH-ADS (Undated) _ Governor George Bush plans to air four
new television spots in New Hampshire and Iowa starting Tuesday,
one in Spanish. By Jill Zuckman.
</P>
<P>
