<HEADLINE>
THE PROBLEMS OF BEING ON ONE'S OWN
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``l'' lifestyle file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1999 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   Actress  &UR; Natalie Portman &LR; , a freshman at Harvard, told TV Guide
Online how tough she's finding academic life.
</P>
<P>
   Stepping into a pile of the wrong stuff on campus one day, she
said ``it got all over my shoes and really freaked me out. So I got
back to the dorm and just left my shoes on the front steps. I
didn't care if they got stolen.
</P>
<P>
   ``I came back and my roommate had seen the shoes sitting there
and put them in my room. I'm like, `Oh, no, what am I going to do?'
</P>
<P>
   ``So I called my mom. She said, `If you've got dog poop on your
shoes, just wipe it off.' I couldn't do it. So I went home for the
weekend and took the shoes, still covered with dog poop, wrapped in
about 20 paper bags. I'm sure you can guess who cleaned off the dog
poop.'' Portman said her mom has always been a big help to her.
