   OPTIONS-MARKETPLACE (New York) _ Some Wall Street firms that
trade options are casting about for ways to retrieve the lost
profitability brought on by the switch to multiple listings. And
some of the practices that they are exploring are not in the best
interests of investors, and may serve to fragment the market rather
than centralize it. By Gretchen Morgenson.
</P>
<P>
   (The story is scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET.)
</P>
<P>
   (Center display)
</P>
<P>
   LOPEZ-BASQUES (Amorebieta, Spain) _ Jose Ignacio Lopez de
Arriortua has long dreamed of building a car factory here in his
Basque hometown. But that dream caused him, by his own reckoning,
to commit the biggest mistake of his life: defecting in 1993 from
the executive suite at General Motors Corp., which declined to
build the advanced, cost-efficient plant he envisioned, and joining
Volkswagen AG, which he said promised to build it but never did.
Still, Lopez clings to his dream, even though it means performing
the seemingly impossible feat of producing his own car from
scratch. By Al Goodman.
</P>
