<P>
   Z-AD-COLUMN (Undated) _ Using a ``z'' at the end of a word _
often in place of the ``s'' that would be there to indicate the
plural form _ is growing increasingly popular in advertising,
marketing and the media. Examples include Beenz, an online
currency; Fritos Racerz, snack chips shaped like race cars; and the
Boyz Channel and the Girlz Channel, cable television networks. By
Stuart Elliott.
