<P>
   ATTENTION EDITORS: Richard Roeper, the popular Chicago Sun-Times
columnist, pays tribute to the American golfer Payne Stewart, who
was killed on Oct. 24 when his Learjet crashed in South Dakota. The
column is available for one-shot purchase from the New York Times
Syndicate.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; THE REEL LIFE OF PAYNE STEWART &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Richard Roeper reflects on how the real life of Payne Stewart
might have played out in the reel life of the movies. He writes:
``Not only can life be coldly indifferent, it often has absolutely
no sense of story arc. No wonder we go to the movies to escape.
Life is messy. Life laughs at the movies. And as we've seen so many
times before, there is no celebrity immunity from sudden, bizarre,
deadly accidents. ''
</P>
