<SLUG> BC-FBC-UCLA-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PLAYMAKERS ABSENT FROM UCLA'S ATTACK
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JON WILNER  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ UCLA's seven points against Cal and Oregon State
are its lowest two-game total in 35 years. Sure, the young
offensive line and rookie quarterback are partly to blame. But the
Bruins can't score without big plays, and they can't make big plays
without their playmakers.
</P>
<P>
   Last year, tailback DeShaun Foster and receivers Danny Farmer
and Brian Poli-Dixon combined for 31 of UCLA's 62 touchdowns.
</P>
<P>
   This year, they have eight.
</P>
<P>
   Poli-Dixon broke his wrist against Fresno State and is out for
the season. Foster sprained his right ankle against Stanford,
played sparingly in two games, then missed Cal and Oregon State.
Farmer played three snaps against Oregon State because of a
strained groin.
</P>
<P>
   Their absence is obvious: In the last two games, the Bruins have
just four plays longer than 20 yards, and two were quarterback
scrambles. As a result, they can't stretch defenses, which puts
more pressure on the struggling line and freshman quarterback Cory
Paus.
</P>
<P>
   ``When you have a young quarterback, you have to find a way to
take the pressure off him,'' offensive coordinator Al Borges said.
``We haven't done that.''
</P>
<P>
   UCLA's daily medical report lists Foster and Farmer as
questionable for Saturday's game against Arizona. Neither is
expected to practice at full speed.
</P>
<P>
   Best-case scenario for Foster: ``He'd practice some and
hopefully play 10-12 plays and give us a spark,'' Bruins coach Bob
Toledo said.
</P>
<P>
   Best-case scenario for Farmer: ``I don't think he could play the
whole game,'' Toledo said, ``but at least he could help us.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Injury update: Cornerback Jason Bell (heel) isn't ready this
week and probably will redshirt. He hasn't played since the Ohio
State game.
</P>
<P>
   Tight end Mike Seidman (sprained shoulder) and linebacker Marcus
Reese (sprained foot) are questionable.
</P>
<P>
   Fullback Durell Price (sprained toe) and linebacker Robert
Thomas (concussion) are probable.
</P>
<P>
   __ The good: Winless on the road, UCLA plays its last three
games in Southern California.
</P>
<P>
   __ The bad: Since starting the 1998 season 10-0, the Bruins have
lost seven of their last 10 games.
</P>
<P>
   __ The ugly: In their last nine quarters _ beginning with the
fourth quarter of the Oregon game _ the Bruins have been outscored
91-7.
</P>
<P>
   __ Odds and ends: For the second consecutive week, Toledo did
not name players of the game.
</P>
<P>
   Defensive end Rusty Williams and tailback Keith Brown will join
the season-long selections, Farmer and Pete Holland, as captains
this week.
</P>
<P>
   __ Latest inductees: UCLA will enshrine 12 former coaches and
athletes into its Hall of Fame on Saturday before the Arizona game.
</P>
<P>
   They are: football players Troy Aikman, Sam Boghosian, Dave
Dalby and Ernie Johnson; golfer Kay Cockerill; softball player
Tracy Compton; three-sport star Denise Corlett; track star and
Olympian Gail Devers; water polo and swim coach Bob Horn; baseball
player Torey Lovullo; gymnast Sharon Shapiro, and track star Kevin
Young.
</P>
<P>
   There is an invitation-only ceremony before kickoff, but the
inductees will be announced at halftime. Aikman is not expected to
attend.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-10-25-99 2056EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
