BRADLEY-CAMPAIGN-BOS, 10-25 -- Bill Braddley signs his autograph on
the arm of Kim Arco, a student at Contoocook Valley Regional High
School, as the candidate was leaving the school's auditorium after
an address to about 800 people earlier this month. Bradley, running
for the Democratic presidential nomination, seems to have a sense
of where he is on the road to his goal, and how he will respond to
his new celebrity. He says he'd still rather share his way of
thinking than deafen his audiences with policy detail. (Tom
Landers/Boston Globe Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT25) BOSTON -- Oct. 25, 1999 -- SCI-ALZHEIMER'S-BOS, 10-25 --
Dr. Dennis Selkoe, of Brigham and Women's Hospital, looks at human
protein cell models as part of his study of Alzheimer's Disease.
Selkoe is one of the most bullish Alzheimer's researchers but is
hardly the only one who thinks Alzheimer's research is moving
toward practical payoffs. (George Rizer/Boston Globe Photo)
