<P>
   (NYT20) NEW YORK -- Oct. 25, 1999 -- COLUMBIA-EDUC, 10-25 --
Columbia University President George Rupp in his office last week.
The university, which during the 1970's and '80's was struggling
with a declining reputation and declining gifts from its alumni,
has edged out Yale as the third-most selective Ivy League college,
after Harvard and Princeton. Rupp, Columbia's
preacher-turned-president, who served as dean of Harvard's Divinity
School and president of Rice University before joining Columbia in
1993, has proved to be a decisive manager and a thoughtful
strategist as well as a tireless fundraiser, many Columbia insiders
say. (Nancy Siesel/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT19) GAZA CITY, West Bank -- Oct. 25, 1999 --
GAZA-WESTBANK-2, 10-25 -- Palestinian leaving Gaza through a new
route to the West Bank hold their identity papers on Monday. The
woman in the foreground is holding a magnetic card issued by the
Palestinian authority. As Israel opened a 27-mile safe passageway
for Palestinians, linking Gaza and the Westbank, desperate Gazans
headed to a ``land of plenty'' -- the West Bank, where they can
make $3 a day instead of $1. (Rina Castelnuovo/New York Times
Photo)
