office in April, 1997. The two Senators sponsored a bill to extend
Medicaid coverage for children. Chafee, one of the dwindling band
of moderate Republicans in the U.S. Senate and a major figure in
Rhode Island politics for 40 years, died Sunday of heart failure.
The death was announced Monday. (Paul Hosefros/New York Times
Photo)
