<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR TUESDAY, OCTOBER 26
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Tuesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-CRICHTON-MOVIE-DEAL-NYT (moved on Sunday, Oct. 24)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, Oct. 24,
about Paramount Pictures' arrangement with the author Michael
Crichton for rights to his new book cited the terms imprecisely.
Mr. Crichton will earn a portion of the studio's receipts from a
movie, not of the film's overall box-office receipts.
</P>
<P>
   BC-IRS-CHARITY-NYT (moved on Wednesday, Oct. 20)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, Oct.
20, about a tax court decision denying deductions to Winn-Dixie
Stores for loans against corporate-owned life insurance
misidentified the carrier of the policies. It was the American
International Group, not the American Heritage Life Insurance
Company.
</P>
<P>
   BC-JUNKMAIL-AD-COLUMN-NYT (moved on Sunday, Oct. 24)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, Oct. 24,
about the proliferation of direct mail, misstated the figures for
sales generated by it. They totaled $421.2 billion in 1998, not
$421.2 million _ as compared with $390 billion in 1997, not $390
million.
</P>
<P>
   BC-ART-NOTES-NYT (moved on Thursday, Oct. 21)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, Oct. 21,
about auction Web sites misstated the planned policy of
Sotheby's.Amazon.com on who will be allowed to sell when the site
goes on line. It will be open to anyone, not just dealers.
</P>
